 126:src/main.cpp  **** // Slew rates (per sample at 48 kHz)
 127:src/main.cpp  **** // Lower value = faster response.
 128:src/main.cpp  **** // NOTE: pitch glide and the amp attack/release are now per-voice (see Voice
 129:src/main.cpp  **** // glide_ms / attack_ms / release_ms), converted to coefficients in the audio
ARM GAS  /tmp/claude-502/ccxENaH3.s 			page 11


 130:src/main.cpp  **** // callback. The constants below are the ones still shared by all voices.
 131:src/main.cpp  **** // Cutoff opening slew. The target is recomputed only at the touch-loop rate
 132:src/main.cpp  **** // (~12-16 Hz) and pressure is quantized to integer %, so a too-fast slew lets
 133:src/main.cpp  **** // each coarse step through as zipper/stair-stepping. ~35 ms interpolates across
 134:src/main.cpp  **** // those steps for a smooth filter sweep while still feeling responsive.
